        <h3>Levels &amp; Dimensions</h3>
        <figure>
          <%= image_tag "levels-dimensions.png" %>

        </figure>
        <p>
          Through experimenting with prototypes, we found a design that worked well to help our customers. The mental model I like
          to use to explain it is a magic pair of binaculars.
        </p>
        <p>
          Imagine looking at a mountain with a set of binoculars. At the widest aperture,
          you see the whole moutain. You turn a dial and you zoom in a bit. Zoom in a little more, and you see a tiny hiker. A little more,
          and the hiker fills out at a higher resolution. At this point, you can only see the peak and all the details of the summit. These are
          the "levels".
        </p>
        <p>
          Now imagine there's another dial on the binoculars. This one changes the visual spectrum&amp;you can now look at the mountain
          in the visible light, infrared, x-ray, gamma, etc. Through these new "dimensions", you can glean new insights about the mountain. Through infrared,
          a campfire is now visible, for example. This way of thinking works really well for displaying monetization performance.
        </p>

