        <h3>More than just performance</h3>

        <figure>
          <%= image_tag "floor-price-modal.png" %>
          <figcaption>
            Floor price control is a core action in SFP. This allows you to be more competitive in the auction and thus optimize
            your earnings for this piece of inventory. The floor price control is embedded in the reporting. If you see your fill rate
            dip, you can take an action within that context.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <p>
          Ok, so I can see how much money I'm making. So what?
        </p>
        <p>
          The real magic in this new design is in combining <strong>performance with management</strong>. If you learn something from reporting, then what? You
          have to leave that context and go into a completely new interface to commit the change. It shouldn't be like that. That experience
          requires too much effort from the user. We wanted it to be easier. So we paired "management" tools like <strong>changing the floor price</strong> (this gives the
          publisher more control on the volume of demand that can compete in the auction) with performance.
        </p>
